import pandas as pd

powers = np.random.lognormal(mean=6.23e13, sigma=10, size=num_samples) # Intensities are extremely high in reality but we scale them down for simulation purposes
cutoff_energies = np.random.uniform(min=3.3, max=95, size=num_samples) 

# Generate random materials and their associated thicknesses (example data points)

# Simplified initial correlation adjustment example (this would be part of a larger, more sophisticated model)

}

# Convert to a numpy array for manipulation and sorting (if needed)
initial_data = np.array(list(zip(*dataframe)))
```
